Describe the principal processes occurring at a specific type of plate boundary (e.g. divergent, convergent, or transform) and how these processes shape its topographic features and influence its tectonic activity (i.e. characteristics of earthquakes and/or volcanoes), using examples.\
\
Divergent boundaries are made by plates drifting away from one another, forming trenches and spreading ridges. Convergent plates are crashing into one another, forming mountains. Transform plates are slipping by one another forming volcanoes.\
